rect:6053576134` finished and spawned several child subagents that are now done or failed, and the group sessions are also showing as done with their child sessions accounted for. The main session shows as completed with the expected endedAt and status values. The telegram:direct session and QLHV ecosystem group are both showing as done with their respective endedAt timestamps, so comparing against the heartbeat state from 06:03 UTC, all the key sessions remain in the same state with no new changes to report. The cron job that monitors every 5 minutes is currently executing this check. I'm seeing the same three cron sessions are still running—the main monitoring cron, the status reporter, and the DTLX monitor—all continuing from the previous check. Telegram group is idle, no new failures, and the pipeline remains healthy, so I'll stay quiet.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Comparing current state (06:05 UTC) vs. last heartbeat (06:03 UTC):\\n\\n**Active sessions (same 3 cron sessions):**\\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` ✅ running (this very instance)\\n- `cron:e7885813` ✅ running (aborted in log but status=running — known/stale)\\n- `cron:6f3323ef` ✅ running\\n\\n**Stable (no change):**\\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` — idle, intact\\n- `telegram:direct:6053576134` — completed normally ✅ (was completed at 05:56 UTC)\\n- No new failures, no new sessions, no blockers surfaced\\n\\n**Pipeline: HEALTHY.** Nothing changed. Silent.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 30691,\n            \"output\": 605,\n            \"totalTokens\": 45673,\n            \"cacheRead\": 13944,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 433,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776