{"type":"message","id":"b17db494","parentId":"72adb926","timestamp":"2026-04-15T06:08:06.700Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The sessions_send timed out. This is a known delivery issue with the Telegram direct session. The cron e7885813 itself has a known issue with delivery timeouts. \n\nSince this is the same delivery issue that's been persistent, I should note this in my response. The cron itself is functioning (it's running, it's the current session), but sessions_send to the Lead is timing out.\n\nI should respond with the status report as per my instructions, and mention the timeout. But since this cron session's job IS to report to Lead via sessions_send, and it timed out... what should I do?\n\nThe cron timed out sending to the Lead. This means the report wasn't delivered. But I'm done with my task.\n\n\nThe task is complete from my end—I've done what I could, but the delivery timeout means the report didn't go through to the Lead.","thinkingSignature":"f685348491c92363b09a211a60b2ff8063b8febe4dfa48c18af70e2ab6689381"},{"type":"text","text":"Delivery timed out — this is the persistent `sessions_send` Telegram issue noted in prior cycles. Report composed and attempted but not received.\n\n**Status summary (this cycle):**\n- 3 active cron sessions confirmed stable (same 3 as previous cycles)\n- No new failures, no blockers\n- `sessions_send` to Lead timed out — delivery issue unresolved"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":180,"output":248,"cacheRead":14084,"cacheWrite":25790,"totalTokens":40302,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776233276969,"responseId":"062e5e3ef059097f1c15a8308544c114"}}
